There is nothing in standard Christianity or in the Bible that
says that you can do that. Nor is there any such doctrine in Buddhism, Judaism, Islam, Hinduism,
or any of the world's other great religions.

<p>
If the ideal spiritual life consists of being guided and manipulated by a &quot;Higher Power&quot;, then
Pinnochio the Puppet is a holy man.

<p>
And the radio-controlled toy cars that you can buy at Radio Shack must be very spiritual too.

<p>
It is also heretical to declare that the ideal Christian life consists
of being a mindless slave who is &quot;Guided&quot; by some &quot;Higher Power&quot;
in a Step-Eleven s&eacute;ance.  I am reminded of a criticism of
